Clearance of corneal crystals in nephropathic cystinosis by topical cysteamine 0.5%.
 A 2-year-old girl with nephropathic cystinosis was successfully treated with topical cysteamine 0.5% to one eye.
 Clearance of crystals from the treated cornea was virtually complete after three months.
 The possibilities and limitations of this form of treatment are discussed.
